Enjoy beautiful Shanghai as host of World Expo 2010 (May-October 2010). For a quick look at the Shanghai Expo "City Rhapsody: The Site of Expo Shanghai," visit http://en.expo2010.cn/sr/video/shipin2.htm.  One-month program to five famous Chinese cities: Beijing, Xi'an, Nanjing, Suzhou/Hangzhou and Shanghai, with side trips to Hong Kong, Sanya (Oriental Hawaii), Yellow Mountain and Tibet. Check the program's website for details, photos, comments, FAQs, etc., at: http://depthome.brooklyn.cuny.edu/bc-china/  Students may choose between three and six credits of study from the following:  1.  History 53: Revolutionary China 2.  Core 1.1: Core Classical Cultures (China) 3.  Core 20.06: Development of the Silk Road 4.  Business 76.5: Asian Business=20 5.  Chinese 1.1: Beginners Chinese; Chinese 2.1: Intermediate Chinese=20 6.  Speech 18.5: Intercultural Communication=20 7.  Speech 23: Business & Professional Communication (cross-cultural perspectives)=20   Program Features: * All courses are taught by Brooklyn College faculty, for CUNY-BC credit=20 * Group travel to five of the most famous and beautiful Chinese cities: Beijing, Xi'an, Nanjing, Suzhou/Hangzhou and Shanghai * Field trips to sites of historical and cultural importance (e.g., TianAnMen Square, the Great Wall, Forbidden City, Summer Palace, Terra Cotta Warriors, ancient city walls, Buddhist temples, Jewish synagogue, Islamic mosques, Suzhou Gardens, silk factory, Cloisonn=E9 factory, the Bund, etc.) * Experience Chinese culture, interact with local people, have a real feel of Chinese life * Travel and sightseeing arranged by professional travel agencies=20 * Side trips to Hong Kong, Sanya (Oriental Hawaii), Yellow Mountain or Tibet=20  =20 Total Estimated Program Cost: $2,898, which includes: * round-trip international tickets (New York to Beijing; Shanghai to New York)=20 * transportation within and between the Chinese cities * nice hotels in all the cities in China=20 * admission tickets to the scenic spots=20   Eligibility: * CUNY undergraduate and graduate students * students from any other U.S. college * CUNY faculty, staff and alumni=20  STOCS scholarships and financial aid are available for qualified students.  For more information: * Visit the program website: http://depthome.brooklyn.cuny.edu/bc-china. * E-mail Professor Lu at CUNYinChina@brooklyn.cuny.edu. * Call 718.951.5225 and ask for Sonia Garrick.  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. subject: ATQ Student Newsletter Is Back!
message: ATQ is back! Your favorite college newsletter--Around the Quads--has a new look and new columns, and we know you'll love what we've done.  ATQ presents features you won't find anywhere else, plus important college news and a comprehensive list of resources on everything from BC academics to career opportunities to what's going on in Brooklyn and New York. We'll include the latest from Student Affairs, and we're continuing our monthly culture column with additional weekly updates (this month we're highlighting the Irish, in honor of St. Patrick's Day). It also features the college's most recent tweets on Twitter and links to what our Bulldogs are doing.  Sound good? Then check it out! ATQ is updated regularly, so bookmark it as one of your favorite sites and visit it regularly at http://atq.brooklyn.cuny.edu.  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. subject:
The Environment and Justice: A Special Talk by Barry Hill, Lawyer
 and Brooklyn College Alumnus
message: Environmental Law and Justice: A Talk by Alumnus Barry Hill, Senior Counsel for Environmental Governance, Office of International Affairs United States Environmental Protection Agency (EPA)  Don't miss this exciting and informative session with one of the nation's most effective advocates for environmental justice. Alumnus Barry Hill is a scholar, teacher, public servant and advocate. He has held senior-level positions as a manager and an attorney in the public and private sectors.  Tuesday, March 23 12:30-2:30pm Multipurpose Room, 411 Library  Register at http://portal.brooklyn.cuny.edu via the Career Tab or e-mail Pamela Brown at pbrown@brooklyn.cuny.edu. subject:
Student Panel on City-based and Sustainability Education, Tuesday,
 March 23
message: Dear Brooklyn College undergraduate student,  **Please reply to the email address given below for information about this event to ensure that it reaches the correct person.  Thank you.**  The Provost's Task Force on City-based and Sustainability Education continues its series of on- and off-campus 'free lunch' events with a student-led panel on Tuesday, March 23.   Come and engage BC students as they share their perspective on taking courses that include city-based learning and sustainability. Lunch will be provided.  The panel begins at 12:30 p.m. in Boylan 2231 and will run until 2:00.  Reservations required; please respond to Tara Mulqueen at tmulqueen@brooklyn.cuny.edu .  We hope to see you there.  Dr. Tammy Lewis, Faculty Fellow for Sustainability Education and Carol L Zicklin Chair in the Honors Academy, Dr. Jocelyn Wills, Faculty Fellow for City-based Education Tara Mulqueen, student Task Force member Dean Donna Wilson  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. subject: Volunteers Needed for Spring Open House
message: Dear Brooklyn College Community:                                          Brooklyn College will once again open its campus to prospective students and their families, and we need you to welcome them! Our Spring Undergraduate Open House will take place on Sunday, April 18, from 11 a.m. to 3 p.m. Help us convey a sense of community while showing off the campus and our programs. You can volunteer as little as two hours or for the entire event. Come out for a day of fun, and showcase your school spirit! Student clubs are also invited to participate; represent your club, represent your campus!  Refreshments will be provided.  To volunteer, contact Derek Rada in the Office of Admissions at DerekR@brooklyn.cuny.edu.     ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. subject: Summer 2010 Study Abroad in China
message: There are a few more seats available for summer 2010 study abroad in China program.  Students can still submit applications to the program during the spring break.  Summer 2010 Study Abroad in China=20  An inexpensive way to travel and study in China: Tentative Dates: May 27-June 23, 2010 =20 See the new Beijing and the new China after the Olympics =20 Enjoy the beautiful Shanghai as host of World Expo 2010 (May to October 2010) . For a quick look at the Shanghai Expo "City Rhapsody: The Site of Expo Shanghai," please go to this link:  http://en.expo2010.cn/sr/video/shipin2.htm=20  One-Month Program to Five Famous Chinese Cities:  Beijing, Xi'an, Nanjing, Suzhou/Hangzhou & Shanghai  With side trips to Hong Kong, Sanya (Oriental Hawaii), Yellow Mountain, Tibet  =20 Check the program's website (photos, comments, FAQ's, etc. ) for details at:=20  http://depthome.brooklyn.cuny.edu/bc-china/  =20  Students may choose 3-6 credits of study from the following:  1. History 53: Revolutionary China=20  2. Core 20.06: Development of the Silk Road  3. Business 76.5: Asian Business=20  4. Chinese 1.1: Beginners Chinese; Chinese 2.1: Intermediate Chinese=20  5. Speech 18.5: Intercultural Communication=20  6. Speech 23: Business & Professional Communication (cross-cultural perspectives)=20  7. CC1.1 Classical Cultures (China)  =20  Program Features:  -All courses are taught by Brooklyn College faculty, for CUNY-BC credit=20  -Group travel to 5 most famous and beautiful Chinese cities: Beijing, Xi'an, Nanjing, Suzhou/Hangzhou & Shanghai=20  -Field trips to sites of historical and cultural importance (e.g., TianAnMen Square, the Great Wall, Forbidden City, Summer Palace, Terra Cotta Warriors, Ancient City Walls, Buddhist Temples, Jewish Synagogue, Great Islamic Mosques, Suzhou Gardens, Silk Factory, Cloisonn=E9 Factory, the Bund, etc)=20  -Experience Chinese culture, interact with local people, have a real feel of Chinese life=20  -Travel and sightseeing are arranged by professional travel agencies=20  -Side trips to Hong Kong, Sanya (Oriental Hawaii), Yellow Mountain or Tibet=20 =20  Total Estimated Program Cost: only $2,898, which includes:  a. round-trip international tickets (NYC to Beijing; Shanghai to NYC)=20  b. transportation within and between the Chinese cities=20  c. nice hotels in all the cities in China=20  d. admission tickets to the scenic spots=20  =20  Eligibility:  1. CUNY undergraduate and graduate=20  2. Students from any other colleges in the U.S.; and=20  3. CUNY faculty, staff and alumni=20   STOCS scholarships and financial Aid are available for qualified students.  =20 For more information about the program,=20  1. Visit the program website: http://depthome.brooklyn.cuny.edu/bc-china  2. E-mail Professor Lu at CUNYinChina@brooklyn.cuny.edu , or  3. 9 Nisan  One who creates a small defect in the body creates a great defect in the soul (Maggid of Mezritch ).  A student spied the great Hillel leaving his academy. He approached the Sage and asked him where he was going. "I am going to do a mitzvah for someone poor and forsaken," Hillel answered. Noting his student's bewilderment, he then explained: "I am going to feed my body. It is totally dependent upon me to look after it."  If someone gives us an object for safekeeping, we have a responsibility to look after it and cannot be derelict in its care. Likewise, our bodies have been entrusted to us, and we have a full obligation to care properly for them.  Too many of us violate our trust by taking unnecessary risks or doing things which are detrimental to our bodies, such as smoking, overeating, or abusing alcohol and drugs. Is it not strange that one who would never think of drinking a non-diet soft drink might not have the least hesitance in smoking a cigarette, even though the harmful effects of smoking are now established beyond a shadow of a doubt?  A Chassidic master observed one of his followers who looked lean and weak. On inquiring, he learned that this man was fasting frequently to atone for his sins. He then told him: "First you set out to ruin your soul, and having achieved this, you are now out to ruin your body as well."   Today I shall ... ... remember that I am fully responsible for the well-being of my body, and I shall take every means to protect it from harm.

subject: Enrollment Services Center Spring Break Hours (March 29-April 6)
message: The Enrollment Services Center, located in the lobby of the West Quad Center, offers registration, financial aid, ID, cashiering and check distribution services to the Brooklyn College community.  Please note that our office hours for the spring break (March 29-April 6) are as follows:  March 29: 9 a.m.-10 p.m. March 30: 9 a.m.-5 p.m. March 31: 9 a.m.-10 p.m. April 1: 9 a.m.-10 p.m. April 2: 9 a.m.-5 p.m. April 3: 9 a.m.-5 p.m. April 4: Closed April 5: 9 a.m.-5 p.m. April 6: 9 a.m.-10 p.m.  Our regular hours of operation are: Monday-Thursday: 9 a.m.-10 p.m. Friday: 9 a.m.-6 p.m. Saturday-Sunday: 9 a.m.-5 p.m.  Please note: Cashiering services end 15 minutes prior to the center's closing.  Enjoy the holiday break!  The Enrollment Services Center Team  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: Summer 2010 Schedule of Classes available online
message: The Summer 2010 Schedule of Classes is now available online at the new consolidated Course Registration information page: http://www.brooklyn.cuny.edu/pub/registration.htm, and in the left-hand quick-access menu in your WebCentral Portal view.    Please note that in the interest of promoting greater environmental sustainability and reducing costs, the college will no longer distribute printed copies of this and future class schedules.  The college will continue to publish compressed PDF versions of the schedules online, which individuals may print in whole or part, if they deem it necessary.    Registration for summer begins on April 13th.  The two summer sessions will run as follows:  Session 1 - June 1-July 8  Session 2 - July 12-August 17   Please make sure to read the Calendar for important deadlines and dates at the above site.  Office of the Registrar       ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: West Quad Center Repair Work
message: Please be advised that the main entrance to the West Quad Center will be closed for waterproofing repairs starting today, March 26, at noon.  We expect the work to take about two weeks to complete and the entrance to reopen  by Friday, April 7.  Until then, enter the West Quad Center by the double glass doors at the caf=E9 near James Hall. =20  The work area will extend from the entrance, along the front of the building towards the tennis courts.  Pedestrians will still have access between the West Quad and the courts, in order to reach the WEB and West Gate.  The interior of the Center will not be affected by the repair work. =20 For your safety, please follow the barricades and posted directions, as well as construction monitors directing pedestrian traffic, when you are in the area.=20  Thank you for your patience and continued cooperation.   ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: Proposed Budget Reductions to Senior Colleges
message: Dear members of the Brooklyn College Community, =20 As you know, budget negotiations in Albany are reaching a crucial point.  Our legislators need to hear from us about the proposed cuts to CUNY's senior colleges.  If approved, these reductions could have a very negative impact on instruction, research, and service support at Brooklyn College.  In addition, support for CUNY's capital projects, including our planned Performing Arts Center and the new science facility need your advocacy. =20 If you have not done so already, I encourage you to take a moment to express your opinion about the proposed budget reductions by contacting individual elected officials directly or by going to CUNY's website, http://www.supportcuny.org, and making use of CUNY's "conference committee letter" to send an e-mail message to the members of the New York State Legislature. =20 Please note that state law prohibits the use of state-owned computers for advocacy purposes.  Your e-mail should be sent either from your home computer or, if you prefer, from another computer location such as the Library Caf=E9 (24 hours), the Library, or the Student Center Computer Corner (Mon-Thurs, noon-8pm). =20 Thank you for considering this important matter.  Your support can truly make a difference. =20 Sincerely,   Karen L. Gould President=20  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

from_: Office of Diversity and Equity Programs <diversity@brooklyn.cuny.edu>
subject: Multicultural Arts Festival 2010
message: Unity through the Arts 2010  A Multicultural Arts Festival  A celebration of cultural diversity, presented by the students and faculty of the Brooklyn College Library, Conservatory of Music, and the Departments of Film, Theater, and Television and Radio.   Admission is free to all events.  Tuesday, April 7 to Friday, May 15 Poster exhibit.   View posters of filmmakers, musicians, playwrights, and writers who explore diversity in their work.   Brooklyn College Library.   Thursday, April 8  Documentary films.   See films that celebrate Brooklyn's diversity, created by the "Community Portraits: Documentary Production" class, a course open to students majoring in film or television and radio.   12:30 p.m., Tanger Auditorium, Brooklyn College Library.    Thursday, April 15  Ti-Jean and his Brothers.   Enjoy this play by Caribbean playwright and Noble Literature Prize-winner Derek Walcott in a workshop performance presented by students majoring in theater.  12:30 p.m., Gershwin Theater.  Annual President's Concert.   Hear music from around the world, including African, Asian, and Western traditions, performed by Conservatory of Music ensembles.  4:30 p.m., Whitman Hall.      ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject:
Professional Skills Training Program: Gain a Competitive Edge in
 the Job Market!
message: Dear Student,  Research shows that 85 percent of your ability to obtain and keep a job is determined by your "soft skills." Prepare yourself for success by attending a Professional Skills Training workshop! The workshops will help you become aware of the skills employers want.  HOW TO REGISTER: Sign up on the career tab of the portal or e-mail Michael Sarrao at msarrao@brooklyn.cuny.edu. For each event, lunch will be provided and a free book on the topic will be given to the first 25 registered students who attend.   10 THINGS EMPLOYERS WANT YOU TO LEARN IN COLLEGE Tuesday, April 13, 12:15-2 p.m., Student Center Do you have the skills needed for college and career success? Do you know what employers look for in candidates? What do you need to know to become more professional in the workforce? Author Bill Coplin will discuss the top 10 things students should learn now instead of learning it the hard way in the real world.     SECRETS OF THE HIGHLY SUCCESSFUL  Tuesday, April 20, 12:15-2 p.m., Student Center Brooklyn College alumni who have achieved the highest level of success in their careers are coming back to share their secrets of success. Do you aspire to own your own company or one day become the head of a company? Do you have questions on what it takes to get there? This panel of illustrious alumni will surely help you get on your way to achieving your career success.  Panelists include:  - Jeffrey Fried, sports agent/lawyer and founder of Fried & Company - Edwin Cohen, principal partner at Prism Capital Partners - Carmen Pacheco, founder of Pacheco & Lugo (first Hispanic women-owned law firm of New York) - Barbara Simmons, director of Urban Fellows Program, NYC DCAS   YOU ARE GRADUATING....NOW WHAT: TRANSITIONING AFTER COLLEGE Tuesday, May 4, 12:15-2 p.m., Student Center Panelists will include recent alumni who work at CBS, PWC, Target, John Wiley and Company and NYC Teaching Fellows. Learn from recent graduates about what to expect and how to strive for stability and success. They will share their stories of transitioning from college to their first "real" job. Ask them questions about what employers expect and what it takes to be successful.     For more information regarding any of these events, please contact Michael Sarrao at msarrao@brooklyn.cuny.edu or 718.951.5696.   Michael Sarrao, Professional Skills Training Coordinator  Natalia Guarin-Klein, Career Education and Training Coordinator          The Willard and Eleanor Archie Professional Skills Training Program Magner Center for Career Development and Internships  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: [reddit] Important information about your account
message: Heads up, SarcasticStaredown:  We've detected some unusual activity on your account and have locked it as an extra security measure.  Your account will be unlocked once a new password has been created.  Resetting your password should be easy.  Visit our password recovery page here:  https://accounts.reddit.com/password  If you do not have an email address associated with your account, a new one can be added in the link above.  If you no longer have access to the email linked to your account, please read the following article for further information:  https://www.reddithelp.com/en/categories/using-reddit/your-reddit-account/im-having-issues-email  We'd like to assure you that Reddit has not been breached.  However, lists of commonly used email/username and password combinations may be found online if another site has been compromised. Because of this, we always recommend using a strong password/email combo that's unique to Reddit only, and setting up two-factor authentication on your account.  You can find instructions for setting up that additional security here:  https://www.reddithelp.com/en/categories/using-reddit/your-reddit-account/how-set-two-factor-authentication  Additional tips for staying on top of your account's security can be found here:  https://www.reddithelp.com/en/categories/using-reddit/your-reddit-account/i-need-help-hacked-or-compromised-account  You can monitor recent account activity here: https://www.reddit.com/account-activity Keep in mind that the geolocation of IP addresses is not an exact science and may occasionally be incorrect, especially on mobile.  - The Reddit Security Team

subject: "Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread" update
message: Dear noreallyimfine,  You are subscribed to the thread "Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread" by kahntrutahn, there have been 1 post(s) to this thread, the last poster was canopen. https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?t=1264953  These following posts were made to the thread: ************ Re: Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?p=55086595#post55086595 Posted by: canopen On: 05-01-2019 10:15 PM  So I deposited to Carbon today after being gone for a while.   The only options given to me were bitcoin and credit card.   The credit card is not a direct option but is a link to a bitcoin processor "Simplex".      Not wanting to get into bitcoin wallets,I chose the second option "credit card" through Simplex.  It actually worked very well, the only difference from using a credit card was I had to upload a photo of the front and back of my driver's license.   After I did that, the deposit went through in a few minutes.  The difference between my CC charge and my deposit was 13%.   I understand that there are various fees in buying and sending bitcoin and I would expect the convenience of sending bitcoin without having to set up a bitcoin purchasing account and a personal wallet might rate a higher fee.   What pissed me off is I was never informed of the fee amount of even the existence of a fee by Carbon or Simplex.  This is bull****.  I complained to Carbon and they replied to the effect of "That's why we give you a 20% bonus. If you don't want to use Simplex here's a link on how to use Bitcoin".  Which of course didn't address my issue of the non-disclosure of the fee amount. However, I am concerned about a message you get on Coinbase after choosing "Request" and before copying the address code. It says:  "Only send Bitcoin (BTC) to this address. Sending any other digital asset, including Bitcoin Cash (BCH), will result in permanent loss."  I know very little about BTC.  Is this message something to worry about?  All I did (I think) was follow the intructions in Carbon cashier and now I have a few days while the transaction is pending to make this is all cool.  Thanks all!  *  To clarify, the reason I am asking is because when you cashout using Bitcoin on Carbon, it is done in terms of dollars, but on Coinbase is said to only use Bitcoin. ---End Quote--- They will send it in BTC, so if you request $1,000 withdrawal they will convert it to BTC and send it.  HOWEVER, there are many many posts on this go check them out, to sum them up you should not send BTC from Carbon to coinbase. ************ Re: Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?p=54647512#post54647512 Posted by: goodsaint On: 01-03-2019 08:23 AM   ---Quote (Originally by CCRod)--- They will send it in BTC, so if you request $1,000 withdrawal they will convert it to BTC and send it.  HOWEVER, there are many many posts on this go check them out, to sum them up you should not send BTC from Carbon to coinbase. ---End Quote--- Financial institutions are not allowed to send/receive funds from gambling sites. Coinbase has closed accounts that they determined were doing such. Hence the need for a buffer/personal wallet to send funds to/from gambling site/Coinbase. ************ Re: Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?p=54649507#post54649507 Posted by: derSchwartz On: 01-03-2019 05:55 PM   ---Quote (Originally by CCRod)--- They will send it in BTC, so if you request $1,000 withdrawal they will convert it to BTC and send it.  HOWEVER, there are many many posts on this go check them out, to sum them up you should not send BTC from Carbon to coinbase. ---End Quote---  ---Quote (Originally by goodsaint)--- Financial institutions are not allowed to send/receive funds from gambling sites. Coinbase has closed accounts that they determined were doing such. Hence the need for a buffer/personal wallet to send funds to/from gambling site/Coinbase. ---End Quote--- Thanks for the warning. I had figured they just used the loophole of "social gaming." But it's not a surprise that there are issues. subject: =?utf-8?Q?=E2=99=A6=20Hurricane=20Pet=20Emergency=20=E2=99=A6?=
message: Avraham =E2=80=94 Hurricane Michael has left thousands of animals homeless:   HELP LABS =E2=96=BA https://Donate.RescueMe.org/lab  DONATE TO OTHER BREEDS =E2=96=BA https://Donate.RescueMe.org  VIEW AVAILABLE PETS =E2=96=BA http://www.RescueMe.org   This hurricane with 155 mph winds was the strongest to hit the U.S. since Andrew in 1992, which left as many as 50,000 animals homeless. Rescue Me will be helping thousands of individuals and shelters in the coming weeks adopt out pets displaced by Michael.  This storm hit close to home for us=E2=80=A6 literally. While we work nationally and internationally helping pets everywhere, Rescue Me also operates its own center for special needs animals on 135-acres in Georgia. I was at the center last night, and we still have contractors on site, as the edge of the eye of Michael passed within 40 miles of us. Here=E2=80=99s a video of our center from a couple years ago (we=E2=80=99ve found homes for more than a quarter million more animals since then): https://www.RescueMe.org/video  This week was supposed to just be a celebration for Rescue Me hitting 777,777 adoptions soon =E2=80=94 and we=E2=80=99re still running our free Petco Gift Card giveaway described on our homepage to celebrate that. Instead, however, it is turning into one of the greatest pet emergencies we have faced since Rescue Me was started.  Please donate to Rescue Me or any of the hundreds of other shelters and rescues who will be helping pets left homeless by the hurricane today. Financial donations are just one way to help. Equally helpful, adopt a pet in need (click view available pets above) or volunteer at a local shelter or rescue.  - Jeff Gold Founder, Rescue Me!                        Email Preferences: http://www.rescueme.org/end?jayjacobsohn@yahoo.com  2020 Pennsylvania Ave. NW, #2001, Washington, DC 20006

=?utf-8?Q?=E2=99=A5=20Help=20Hurricane=20Pets=20=E2=99=A5=20Free?=

message: Avraham =E2=80=94 Rescue Me is about to hit 777,777 adoptions, and we need your help more than ever. Hurricane Michael may leave thousands of pets homeless this week. subject:
=?utf-8?Q?=E2=96=BA=20Lab=20Rescue=20=E2=96=BA=20Helpful=20Hints?=
 =?utf-8?Q?=20for=20Adopters?=
message: Dear Avraham,  Thank you for using http://www.RescueMe.org to email about Lab Dogs for adoption.  I'll answer some questions you may have:  WHEN WILL SOMEONE REPLY TO MY EMAIL?  Your are more likely to receive a quick reply if you email about multiple animals, not just one.  Rescue Me acts as a referral service, the people you email are either individuals or representatives of rescue groups we work with, but are not a direct part of Rescue Me!  Some may respond quickly, others may take a few days to respond or may not respond at all.  Try not to put all your hopes on adopting one particular animal.  HOW CAN I INCREASE MY CHANCES OF ADOPTING?  Click below to sign up for free Rescue Alerts to get notified when new animals of the breed(s) you select are posted:          http://www.RescueMe.org/alerts  WHAT IF SOMETHING IS WRONG WITH A POST, OR SOMEONE DOESN'T GET BACK TO ME?  Click 'Problems/Corrections' at the bottom of a post to report this.  WHAT IF I FIND OUT AN ANIMAL HAS ALREADY BEEN ADOPTED?  Help us keep Rescue Me updated, click 'Mark as Unavailable' at the bottom of that post.  HOW CAN I HELP RESCUE ME HELP MORE ANIMALS?  Please copy/paste our website address   www.RescueMe.org   into your Facebook status, to share our service with friends and family.  Remember, each time you rescue instead of buying a pet, you save many lives, not just one.  In addition to saving the rescued animal, you leave more room at shelters and rescue groups for others in need.  If you buy from a pet store or breeder, somewhere else an animal will likely be euthanized due to overpopulation, and your purchase will encourage breeders to breed even more.  There are far too many animals of all types, including purebreds =E2=80=94 millions end up euthanized every year.  We intend not to just reduce this number, but to work toward completely stopping this practice in the years ahead.  We can only do so with YOUR help, so please rescue!  Sincerely,  Jeff Gold Founder, Rescue Me! http://www.RescueMe.org   P.S. Like what we do? Consider donating: https://Donate.RescueMe.org/lab  (Donate as a gift, and we'll mail a free card.)      TERMS OF SERVICE: Rescue Me! acts only as a referral service for adoptions. Rescue Me! has not screened or evaluated animals posted on our website, the people who post them, or those who apply to adopt. Sole responsibility for animals belongs to the animal control facilities, rescue organizations, and individuals owning and/or adopting these animals. Rescue Me! cannot guarantee any information posted on our website, and accepts no responsibility or liability whatsoever related to injury or property damage that may be caused by an animal or person you may meet using this website. Any adopted animal should be taken to a veterinarian. BREEDING OF ADOPTED ANIMALS IS PROHIBITED. Dogs and cats must be spayed or neutered before or immediately after adoption, unless a health condition prevents this. Use of the Rescue Me! site constitutes acceptance of these terms.

subject: "Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread" update
message: Dear noreallyimfine,  You are subscribed to the thread "Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread" by kahntrutahn, there have been 1 post(s) to this thread, the last poster was TheStacker. https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?t=1264953  These following posts were made to the thread: ************ Re: Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?p=54262812#post54262812 Posted by: TheStacker On: 09-14-2018 01:29 PM  I appreciate you writing up and sharing this info, but would be nice if you had added a step #2 for deposit:  "Wait 6 days"  I would have used another option if you had mentioned the 6-day hold they put on your money after depositing.  I take it there's no way to undo the deposit now?     ---Quote (Originally by bufo alvarius)--- Sure!  Deposit: -Deposit on Coinbase with your bank account. -Get on Blockchain and select "request" (lower right). -Copy your wallet address by tapping it - which will automatically copy it. -Go back to Coinbase and go to 'accounts' and select 'BTC Wallet' -Select the arrow top right of screen and put in the amount of USD you want to send to block chain and hit 'Next' -Paste your blockchain address in and hit sent. -Once the funds appear in your blockchain app (which should be pretty fast) -On Carbon - go to deposit + enter the amount + add the 30% weekly bonus or whatever bonus you can, copy the bitcoin address on there and paste that in blockchain as the address you send to. Funds should be in there pretty much immediately.   Withdraw: -Enter amount, paste in your blockchain address + enter your pin. Has been taking about 5 business days for most people. -Go to Coinbase and copy your bitcoin address (accounts->BTC wallet-> the square thing next to the arrow top right). -Go to blockchain -> send -> paste address + put in amount and you're all set.. -In coinbase, withdraw to your bank account. ---End Quote---    All the best, Two Plus Two Poker Forums  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ Unsubscription information:  To unsubscribe from this thread, please visit this page: https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/subscription.php?do=removesubscription&type=thread&subscriptionid=7697837&auth=50feaeb11d1bda5c51d01cd52823b218

message: Dear noreallyimfine,  You are subscribed to the thread "Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread" by kahntrutahn, there have been 2 post(s) to this thread, the last poster was bufo alvarius. https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?t=1264953  These following posts were made to the thread: ************ Re: Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?p=54153846#post54153846 Posted by: NZdice On: 08-12-2018 07:50 PM   ---Quote (Originally by bufo alvarius)--- Sure!  Deposit: -Deposit on Coinbase with your bank account. -Get on Blockchain and select "request" (lower right). -Copy your wallet address by tapping it - which will automatically copy it. -Go back to Coinbase and go to 'accounts' and select 'BTC Wallet' -Select the arrow top right of screen and put in the amount of USD you want to send to block chain and hit 'Next' -Paste your blockchain address in and hit sent. -Once the funds appear in your blockchain app (which should be pretty fast) -On Carbon - go to deposit + enter the amount + add the 30% weekly bonus or whatever bonus you can, copy the bitcoin address on there and paste that in blockchain as the address you send to. Funds should be in there pretty much immediately.   Withdraw: -Enter amount, paste in your blockchain address + enter your pin. Has been taking about 5 business days for most people. -Go to Coinbase and copy your bitcoin address (accounts->BTC wallet-> the square thing next to the arrow top right). -Go to blockchain -> send -> paste address + put in amount and you're all set.. -In coinbase, withdraw to your bank account. ---End Quote--- 1st off, thank you so much man, you rock!:D The only question, is that the way you find your blockchain address, is that's what pops up when you click on "request,"  right? But, when withdrawing from Carbon, you don't have actually use the "request" tab on Blockchain, right? It's confusing also because on Blockchain, it says that the address changes for every transaction. I'm  guessing that because of that, I also have to wait until the 1st transaction clears, until sending the next amount since I will have to use a different address. ************ Re: Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?p=54156793#post54156793 Posted by: bufo alvarius On: 08-13-2018 05:50 PM  No problem - yeah it's the one that pops up when you hit 'request' - you just copy and paste that into Carbon when you cash out. You have to wait until the previous cash out goes through to cash out regardless which sucks (so you can't have more than one pending). You can however cancel the pending cash out and then do one for more/less money. Even if you still have it, a bitcoin deposit is usually needed to unlock the bitcoin withdrawal option. ************ Re: Merge Network: Carbon/ Sportsbook/ PlayersOnly - Deposit/ Withdrawal Thread https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/showthread.php?p=53966062#post53966062 Posted by: kahntrutahn On: 06-22-2018 09:12 AM   ---Quote (Originally by barbwire)--- anyone know if it's necessary to deposit with bitcoin in order to withdrawal with it? or will carbon let me use my card and then w/d with btc?  ty ---End Quote--- I can't say what their policy is exactly, but what you mention is unlikely. The reason being is that there is liability for credit card deposits. Long-standing liability that can last 6-12 months for a site. However, Bitcoin is non-refundable.   The fear, and this happens in practice, is that a player deposits with a credit card, plays, and requests a withdrawal. A site pays it in crypto-currency and then, months later, the player initiates a charge back on the credit card. Now the gambling site is screwed with zero ways to recover their lost funds.  Very few people are allowed to do CC deposits and Crypto withdrawals, industry wide. In fact, I only know of it happening in a few select cases to satisfy long-standing whales. Otherwise, most sites learned very quickly that this was a bad idea.  -- Kahn   All the best, Two Plus Two Poker Forums  ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ Unsubscription information:  To unsubscribe from this thread, please visit this page: https://forumserver.twoplustwo.com/subscription.php?do=removesubscription&type=thread&subscriptionid=7697837&auth=50feaeb11d1bda5c51d01cd52823b218

message: *** PLEASE DO NOT REPLY TO THIS AUTOMATED MESSAGE ***	 	 	 Your electric statement from The Illuminating Company is available for review.  To access your account securely online, visit https://www.firstenergycorp.com/log_in.   	 	   	    Account Number:  11 01 21 4107 3 9	    Due Date:        06/06/2018	    Amount Due:      $54.29	    Service Address: AVRAHAM JACOBSOHN                  33332 VINE ST APT 104                  EASTLAKE OH 44095	 	 To view your monthly bill inserts, which include state-mandated messages, newsletters and other important information, please visit https://www.firstenergycorp.com/billinserts.	 	 If you would like to receive text or email payment and outage alerts, go to https://www.firstenergycorp.com/connect.	 	 For questions or concerns, please email us at https://www.firstenergycorp.com/contactus, or call 1-800-589-3101.	 	 Special Notice:	 We are warning customers about a scam involving a telephone caller posing as an electric company employee threatening to shut off power unless an immediate payment is made using a pre-paid debit card such as a Green Dot card.  Although we may phone customers to remind them that a payment is past due, we would explain how a payment can be made using one of our many payment options.  If you receive a call demanding immediate payment using a specific option, please contact us at 1-800-589-3101. subject: Annual Conference of the College Language Association
message: Brooklyn College is hosting the 70th annual convention of the College Language Association (CLA) at the Brooklyn Bridge Marriott in downtown Brooklyn. This year's conference, "Freedom's Visions and Urban Landscapes: Spaces and Places in Language and Literature," will take place from Thursday, April 8, to Saturday, April 10.   This year's keynote speaker is Myriam Chancy, a professor of English at the University of Cincinnati. Chancy's address, "'Harvesting' Port-au-Prince, Haiti: Zora Neale Hurston's Literary (Dis)Articulation of Being," will take place during the CLA banquet on Friday, April 9, at 7:30 p.m.   In addition, Chancy will give a lecture about the mnemonics and politics of Haitian women's historical representation and contemporary (spiritual) survival on Thursday, April 8, 12:15 to 1:30 p.m. in the Gold Room, Student Center.  Registration starts today, Wednesday, April 7, 4-7 p.m. The CLA Executive Committee will hold its pre-convention meeting at 6:30 p.m. at the hotel.  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. subject:
REVISED Schedule for Making up Classes Missed due to Snow on
 February 26th
message: Dear Students,  I write to inform you of the REVISED schedule for making up classes missed due to the snow storm on Friday, February 26th.   Missed UNDERGRADUATE CLASSES will be made up on Wednesday, May 19th, i.e., May 19th will follow a Friday class schedule for UNDERGRADUATE COURSES. UNDERGRADUATE FINAL EXAMS originally scheduled for May 19th will be held on Wednesday, May 26th. Thus the UNDERGRADUATE final exam period will extend from May 20th through May 26th.  For GRADUATE CLASSES, however, May 19th will be the first day of the final exam/class meeting period, i.e., GRADUATE CLASSES that meet during the semester on Wednesdays will have their final exam/class meeting on May 19th. The GRADUATE final exam/class meeting period will extend therefore from May 19th through May 25th.  Please note: May 26th will also serve as a makeup day for finals missed or not administered on May 19th and 20th due to religious observance. subject: Get Your Summer Internship Now! There's still time.
message: Dear Student,  Summer internships are the way to go!  It's not too late to get a good summer internship that will further your career goals and opportunities. Getting a great internship is essential to landing the job you want after college. The Magner Center's Nuts and Bolts of Landing an Internship Workshop will take you through the process from the requirements of participation in the internship program, to searching, finding and applying for an internship. from_: "William A. Tramontano, Provost and Vice President for Academic Affairs" <sems@brooklyn.cuny.edu>
subject: Retention Task Force Town Hall Meetings
message: Dear All,   In November 2009, President Gould asked me to lead a task force consisting of 18 faculty and administrative staff to study the means by which the College can assist undergraduate students in progressing toward and completing their degrees. The President asked us to look at the policies and practices in place at Brooklyn College, to compare them to nationally identified best practices with regard to student success, and to present her with a set of recommendations for improvements that can and should be made at Brooklyn College to support student success.   The Task Force has completed its work and is now seeking your input on our findings and recommendations so that we can shape our final report to President Gould.   We have posted a set of documents on the WebCentral Portal for you to review and we are seeking your comments either via email or in person at two Town Hall meetings:   Retention Task Force Town Hall Meeting Schedule  Tuesday, April 20th, 12:15 PM - 2:15 PM, Room 3139 Boylan   Tuesday, April 20th, 5 PM - 6:30 PM, Tanger Auditorium, Library   The Summary of the Task Force's Recommendations, a brief report that includes statistics on retention and graduation rates at Brooklyn College, and an email comments form for you to use in sending us your thoughts are posted on the WebCentral portal at http://www.brooklyn.cuny.edu/portal/retention for you to review.   The Task Force members and I hope to see you at one of the Town Halls next week!     Sincerely,  William A. Tramontano Provost and Vice President for Academic Affairs      ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: Invitation: Building Bridges Conference - Register by April 22nd
message: FIRST ANNUAL BUILDING BRIDGES CONFERENCE: Community Partnerships and Learning  May 6 and 7, 2010 Brooklyn College   Brooklyn College, Student Center Thursday, May 6, 2010  Field trip to Plumb Beach Friday, May 7, 2010  At this two-day conference, you'll learn how to put some community-based action into your education!   Conference highlights include:   * Keynote address by Professor Beverly Wright, Dillard University, New Orleans, environmental justice scholar and activist, and founder of the Deep South Center for Environmental Justice.   * Panel presentations from those that have developed and maintained community partnerships.    * Workshops on how to create partnerships and link up with already existing partnerships that range from health, city agriculture, food and history.  * Community Partner Fair-Networking! Share your work and learn about the projects of other community groups, faculty and students   * Field trip to Plumb Beach. See an example of what students and our community partners at the National Park Service are doing to preserve Plumb Beach. Lunch at Floyd Bennett Field.   The conference is free, but space is limited! The first 100 registrants receive a Sustainable Brooklyn College travel mug.  Registration deadline: Thursday, April 22. For more information, please visit:  http://www.brooklyn.cuny.edu/bc/spotlite/pdf/sustain_ed.pdf  To register, visit: http://www.brooklyn.cuny.edu/pub/sustainability.htm   ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. subject:
Last day to officially withdraw from Spring '10 classes - April
 20th
message: The last day to withdraw from any Spring 2010 course(s) is April 20th. When you withdraw from courses, a W grade will stay on your transcript but it will not affect your GPA. If you are receiving financial aid, you are advised to speak to a financial aid advisor before withdrawing from courses.   You may withdraw from any course(s) online via WebCentral (https://portal.brooklyn.edu) or in the Enrollment Services Center located in the lobby of the West Quad Center.  The following students may not withdraw online and must obtain the signature of a counselor from the respective department before returning the completed withdrawal form to the Enrollment Services Center by 10:00p.m. on April 20th.  * First semester freshmen, second semester freshmen, first semester transfer students and students on academic probation must report to the Center for Academic Advisement and Student Success (3207 Boylan Hall).   * SEEK students must report to the SEEK Department (2208 Boylan Hall).  * ESL students must report to the ESL Department (1414 Ingersoll Hall).  * TOCA students must report to the TOCA Department (3219 Boylan Hall).  * Students withdrawing from English 1 must report to the English Department (2308 Boylan Hall).  Absolutely no withdrawals will be allowed after April 20th.       ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. message: 2010-2011 Financial Aid Information is now available on the "Financial Aid Flash"  http://www.brooklyn.cuny.edu/pub/1401.htm  For financial aid and information for the 2010-2011 academic year, please visit the Student Web Central of Brooklyn College and access the latest "Financial Aid Flash" for more details. (Cut and paste the above hyperlink.)  * Information on summer 2010 financial aid * Direct Loan applications and checklists are available on-line. * Other information  Please remember that you must file your FAFSA before May 1st in order to meet the College's deadline for maximum financial aid consideration. subject:
Register now! Building Bridges: Community Partnerships and Learning
 May 6-7
message: Dear Brooklyn College Student,  Now that you've celebrated Earth Day, don't forget to register for Brooklyn College's First Annual Building Bridges: Community Partnerships and Learning. =20  Conference highlights include:  =A7        Keynote address by Dr. Beverly Wright, Dillard University, New Orleans, environmental justice scholar and activist, and founder of the Deep South Center for Environmental Justice.=20  =A7        Panel presentations from those that have developed and maintained community partnerships. =20  =A7        Workshops on how to create partnerships and link up with already existing partnerships that range from health, city agriculture, foods, and history.  =A7        Community Partner Fair-Networking! Share your work and learn about the projects of other community groups, faculty, and students=20  =A7        Field trip to Plumb Beach. See an example of what students and our community partners at the National Park Service are doing to preserve Plum Beach. Lunch at Floyd Bennett Field.=20   The conference is free but space is limited! The first 100 registrants receive a Sustainable Brooklyn travel mug!  Registration deadline: April 26, 2010 (late registrants will be permitted as space permits)=20  For more info: http://www.brooklyn.cuny.edu/pub/2078.htm  To register:  http://bcbuildingbridges.eventbrite.com/  Sponsored by the Provost's Task Force for City-Based and Sustainability Education at Brooklyn College  =20    ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: Marketing Photography on Campus This Week
message: The Office of Communications and Marketing is currently working with outside photographers as part of the creation of new promotional materials for student recruitment as well as the general marketing of the College. This is an important project that will help the College attract students, increase our visibility and strengthen our message.   The photographer, Bob Handelman; his assistant, Jason Rogers; and the account manager for our marketing firm, BethAnne Hoffmann-Garcia, will be on campus Monday, April 26, to Friday, April 30. While individual students have already agreed to participate in photo shoots, other general shots of the campus and our facilities may inadvertently include other members of the College community (including faculty and staff) who have not personally agreed to be included.   The photographers are very sensitive to the wishes of our students and the academic mission of the community. All precautions will be made to ensure that classes and other activities during the week will not be disturbed. If you do not wish to be included in a shot, please let the photographers know and they will ensure that you will not be in the frame.  However, we ask for your cooperation and understanding as we complete this stage of the project and would appreciate any help and assistance you can extend.   Thank you.   Pat Willard Interim Director, Office Communications and Marketing  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: BC Feedback (Student Evaluation of the Faculty)
message: BC FEEDBACK FOR SPRING 2010 IS ONLINE  You've taken the class, you've done the work....Now tell us what you think!  We want to hear your opinion in your own words!  *   *   *   *   *   *   *   *  This semester the BC Feedback period will run from April 27 through May 26. Because it's completely online, you can sit at home with a cup of coffee, jump on a computer at the Library Caf=E9, or take a quick break at work to let us know what you think!  By evaluating the professors who taught you this semester, you'll provide a great service to your fellow students and the College at large.  Plus, only participants completing all of their evaluations receive these great benefits:  * Lottery Prizes - A chance to win cash prizes of $250, $100 and $50.  * Early notification of course grades via eGrade, in some instances up to 14 days before grades are posted.  * Early access to your fellow students' ratings and comments about their professors and courses in time for Fall 2010 semester program changes.  * The opportunity to play an important role in enhancing academic excellence at Brooklyn College.  Student evaluations are a key component of the College's review of faculty performance. Your feedback will help faculty and departments provide the best possible instruction. All responses are completely anonymous, and your identity will not be associated with your evaluations.  It's easy and only takes a few minutes! Just log on to the WebCentral Portal (http://portal.brooklyn.edu) and look for the BC Feedback tab for the evaluation links and status page.  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: Jump Start Your Career Today
message: Did you know that 60 percent of students change their major?  Did you know people change careers, not jobs, at least five times during their lifetime?  If you are undecided about or are considering switching your major, or you are exploring career options, sign up for the Magner Center's Finding the Right Major and Career Workshop! Deciding on the right major can be perplexing. Identifying your skills, abilities and values is key to making the right decision.    This workshop will help clarify how a realistic decision can be made.    Remaining workshops for the spring semester:  Thursday, May 6, 12:30-2 p.m., 2207 James Hall  Wednesday, May 12, 5-6:30 p.m., 1309 James Hall   Registration is required for the workshop:  Log on to http://portal.brooklyn.edu via "Career" tab or e-mail  zbaynes@@brooklyn.cuny.edu.  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject:
Magner Internship Alert: There's Still Time to Land a Great Summer
 Internship
message: Summer internships are the way to go!  It's not too late to get a good summer internship that will further your career goals and opportunities. Getting a great internship is essential to landing the job you want after college.   The Magner Center's Nuts and Bolts of Landing an Internship Workshop will take you through the process from the requirements of participation in the internship program, to searching, finding and applying for an internship. Come and get the answers to your most pressing questions.     The remaining workshop dates are as follows:  Tuesday, May 4, 12:30-2 p.m., 2207 James Hall   *Tuesday, May 11, 5-6 p.m., 1309 James Hall  To register:  1)  Log onto BC Web Central, https://portal.brooklyn.edu, and select the Career Tab.  2)  Go to the Workshop Registration Channel to view the center's events and select the Register Button.  * Employers are not scheduled for evening and weekend workshops.  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. subject: Evaluate Your Instructors! Great Benefits!
message: Dear AVRAHAM JACOBSOHN:  We noticed that you have not yet completed all of your Spring 2010 course evaluations. To access these evaluations, just log in to the WebCentral portal (https://portal.brooklyn.edu) by May 26th and select each of your courses to give us your feedback.   By taking just a few minutes to complete all your BC Feedback evaluations, you'll receive:  +++ Lottery Prizes: You'll have a chance to win cash prizes of $250, $100 and $50.  +++ Immediate notification of your course grades as soon as they are submitted by your professors. Students who have not completed 100% of their evaluations will need to wait until June 2nd at the earliest to receive their grades.   +++ Early access to your fellow students' rating and comments about their professors and courses in time to make schedule changes for the fall 2010 semester. Other students will not have access to this information until after the drop/add period during the fall semester.   All BC Feedback responses are completely anonymous! Thank you for your help in enhancing teaching and learning at Brooklyn College!  Sincerely,  Jerry Mirotznik Associate Provost  		This email was sent to: AVRAHAM JACOBSOHN <jayjacobsohn@yahoo.com>

subject: Second Semester Registration
message: Dear Student,  This is Peter Pampalone, the First Year Specialist, and once again the time has come for you to register for classes.  I hope that this past semester has been an interesting and exciting experience for you. This is the second reminder that you need to schedule your appointment on the S.M.A.R.T. system in order to register for the Fall 2010 semester. Just as last semester, all you need to do is log onto the S.M.A.R.T. system to choose the time you will be coming in to register. Please do not hesitate--available appointment times are quickly being taken, and these are the only days you will be able to come to register for classes. We look forward to seeing you at registration.    Regards,  Peter L. Pampalone First Year Specialist CAASS 3207 Boylan Hall 718.951.5471

subject: The Enrollment Services Center's New Queue System
message: No more standing in line! With our new queue system, you can sit while you wait!    Starting May 10, in an effort to continue providing quality services to our students, the Enrollment Services Center (ESC) has been operating through our brand-new queuing system. The system will allow you to print a ticket for the section of the ESC you would like to visit. You can then take a seat in our waiting area until your number is called.  The system won't work without your help, so we ask that you follow these simple steps when visiting the ESC:  * When you enter the ESC, go to the kiosks located to the left of the main entrance.  * Use the touch screen to choose the area you need help in and take your printed ticket.  * Take a seat in the waiting area and relax (please don't lose your ticket!).  * When your number is called, it will be announced via a speaker in the lobby and will appear on the new LCD screens behind the counter.  * Our counter stations will be numbered so you can find the representative waiting to help you.  * If you would like to visit another station at the ESC, please be sure to let the staff member behind the counter know to ensure you are placed in that service's queue.  Thank you in advance for your help in making this a success, and we look forward to assisting you.  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: Summer 1 courses and cancellation of under-enrolled sections
message: Dear Brooklyn College student,  If you plan to take a course in summer session 1, please register for it as soon as possible.  The College is making every effort to run courses that students need to advance toward graduation, and we are using enrollments to make those determinations.  All courses must meet minimum enrollments in order to run; we begin review and cancellation of under-enrolled sections on Monday, May 17.    Please do not delay registering for your summer 1 program.  If you have questions about how to fund your summer tuition and fee bill, you may visit the Enrollment Services Center or review the information on the website: http://www.brooklyn.cuny.edu/pub/billpay.htm  If you have other questions, please contact your major advisor or see an advisor in CAASS or your special program; they will be happy to assist you.  Sincerely, Dean Donna Wilson   ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: Registration appointment confirmation - BC SMART
message: AVRAHAM JACOBSOHN,  Thank you for using SMART.  You have made an appointment as a second semester freshman student to register for courses on:   Jun 18 2010 11:00AM in the West Quad Center  Your appointment confirmation number is: 8197621781  Please be advised, except for special circumstances no one other than the student who is registering will be permitted to enter the registration area.   During your appointment you will attend a workshop, meet with an advisor in a group setting, and schedule your classes for  both the Summer and Fall 2010 semesters. The entire registration process can take up to 3 hours, so please plan accordingly.  Please bring with you:   A printout of this confirmation. This is your admission slip to the registration site. You may not be admitted if you are not on the session roster.    A pen.   A method of payment (cash, check, money order, major credit card).   Any student copies of Advanced Placement Scores, College Now transcripts, or current college transcripts.    Please remember that your immunization must be cleared 2 business days prior to your registration appointment. If you are not immunization compliant at the time of your appointment, you will not be allowed to register. Immunization records will not be collected at the registration site. The Office of Immunization and Health Programs can be contacted at hpo@brooklyn.cuny.edu, 718-951-4505, 0710 James Hall.    If you need to change your appointment you can do so at any time through the SMART system accessible from the BC WebCentral Portal at http://portal.brooklyn.edu.    Email smart@brooklyn.cuny.edu if you have any questions or difficulties.

subject: Corrected Dates for Last Day of Classes / Final Exams
message: We'd like to correct an error in today's Brooklyn College Weekly regarding the last day of classes and first day of finals.  Due to snow days this spring semester, the College must make a slight adjustment to its schedule.  The last day of undergraduate classes will be Wednesday, May 19. Classes on that day will follow a FRIDAY schedule. Undergraduate final exams begin on Thursday, May 20. Undergraduate final exams originally scheduled for May 19 will now be held on Wednesday, May 26.  For graduate classes, Wednesday, May 19, will be the first day of the final exam/class meeting period (i.e., graduate classes met on Wednesdays during the semester will have their final exam/class meeting on May 19). Graduate final exams will run from May 19 through Tuesday, May 25.  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. subject: End-of-Semester Message from the Library
message: Brooklyn College Students:=20  As we come to the end of another academic year, the library would like to make sure you are aware of a few of our policies. We'd also like to highlight a few services that may help you with your last-minute studying and research:  * Students requiring research help after library hours can go to http://library.brooklyn.cuny.edu. Click the Ask-a-Librarian button on the home page, then click on the "chat"  button and ask a question, which will be fielded by Brooklyn College Library staff or by any librarian participating in our network of reference librarians. This on-demand reference service spans all hours of the day or night, whether or not the physical building is open.  * Students can borrow a laptop to help finish last-minute work. Laptops can be borrowed for one to three days, and are available at the New Media desk on second floor of the library.  * During the exam period, the main library is open Monday-Thursday, 8 a.m.-midnight; Friday, 8 a.m.-5 p.m.; Saturday and Sunday, 10 a.m.-6 p.m. The Library Caf=E9 is on a 24/7 schedule and will be staffed for the duration of exams.  * Summer Hours begin after Memorial Day: Monday and Thursday, 9 a.m.-6 p.m.; Tuesday and Wednesday, 9 a.m.-9 p.m.; and Friday, 9 a.m.-5 p.m. The library will be closed on Saturday and Sunday.=20  * The library has a number of group study rooms available. These can be reserved by contacting the Circulation Desk. Only parties of two or more can reserve the rooms. Policies are located at http://dewey.brooklyn.cuny.edu/library/about/events/index.php?view=3Droom_map&unit=3Dgs.  * Regarding quiet study space: The library does not have designated silent study areas but requests that students be courteous to their fellow users, utilize headphones for personal listening devices, put cell phones on vibrate and take any cell phone conversations to the stairwells.  * Remember, drinks are permitted in the library as long as they are in no-spill containers, such as bottles with caps or go-cups. Food, however, is not permitted in the library.  Thank you, and good luck on your final exams!  =20 Stephanie R. Walker Chief Librarian and Executive Director of Academic Information Technology Brooklyn College  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

subject: Support the Vallone Scholarship Program
message: Dear Members of the Brooklyn College Community,  Every year, the Peter F. Vallone Scholarship helps thousands of CUNY students pursue an undergraduate degree.  This semester, well over one thousand students at Brooklyn College received financial assistance from this source.  Unfortunately, renewal is not guaranteed as this is just one of hundreds of programs that compete for City Council support.  Members of the New York City Council need to be reminded of the importance of the Vallone Scholarship before the city budget is adopted in mid-June.=20  You can take action now to protect this scholarship.  Please use the http://www.supportcuny.org website, scroll down to the 2010/11 New York City Council Campaign, select the appropriate letter to send to members of the City Council, and urge them to support our Vallone scholars.  Please note that state law prohibits the use of state-owned computers for advocacy purposes.  Your e-mail should be sent either from your home computer or, if you prefer, from another computer location such as the Library Caf=E9 (24 hours), the Library, or the Student Center Computer Corner (Monday-Thursday, noon-8 p.m.).  Thank you.  Sincerely,  Dr. Karen L. Gould=20 President   ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

The grade is ABS -- ABSENT FROM FINAL.       This is the original grade that was submitted by your instructor after final exams. If the grade has been changed since then, this e-mail does not reflect that change. Please note that although your grade has been submitted by your instructor, it may take 5-10 business days for it to appear on your transcript.       Due to new CUNY rules, ABS and FAB grades do not appear on student transcripts. Instead, the ABS grade will automatically be translated into an INC grade in WebSIMS and transcripts, and an internal transcript comment will indicate that the INC was assigned on account of a missed final. This ABS grade will eventually either be changed to a standard grade if you are allowed to take a make-up absentee final exam, or an FIN if that does not occur.         BC's internal systems such as the WebCentral Portal will show the ABS grade until it is resolved. You can verify the ABS status of the course in the WebCentral Portal under the My Info tab, in "My Schedule and Grades" channel.            To view your transcript or term grade, simply point your browser to the BC WebCentral at http://portal.brooklyn.edu. "WebSIMS" channel will be available on "eServices" tab. You can also use "WebSIMS" shortcut link in the left sidebar regardless of which tab is currently active. subject:
Need a Job or Internship? Sign Up for Summer Career Workshops at
 the Magner Center
message: Dear Student,  Gain a Summer Advantage: Set Sail with the Magner Center  Check out our summer workshop schedule and learn how to navigate this economic market. The Magner Center is open during the summer, and workshops will be available for Summer Session I. It is not too late to gain valuable career experience by acquiring an internship. Attend the "Nuts and Bolts of Landing an Internship" workshop.   ALUMNI ONE-SHOT JOB SEARCH WORKSHOP=20 Tuesday, June 1, 12:30-2:30 p.m., 1309 James Hall  Open to all recent alumni. Learn how to navigate in this current economic market. Meet with guest speakers for a panel discussion. Learn about which industries/careers are still in demand, what employers are looking for in candidates, where the emerging "green" sectors are and how to obtain a job in this recovery economy.  =20 ONE-SHOT JOB SEARCH WORKSHOP=20 Tuesday, June 8, 12:30-2 p.m., 1309 James Hall Wednesday, June 23, 12:30-2 p.m., 1309 James Hall  This workshop combines r=E9sum=E9 writing, interviewing skills and e-recruiting/job search into one convenient session. Completing this workshop qualifies students to participate in the Magner Intern and Job Recruitment program.=20   NUTS AND BOLTS OF LANDING AN INTERNSHIP Wednesday, June 9, 5:30-6:30 p.m., 1309 James Hall Tuesday, June 15, 12:30-1:30 p.m., 1309 James Hall  Students seeking internships are required to complete the Nuts and Bolts workshop. It's no secret that an internship can help you get a job, but how can you make sure you get the best internships? This internship seminar will take you through the process, from the requirements for participation in the internship program to searching, finding and applying for an internship. Come to the seminar to get the answers to your most pressing questions.  =20 Register at http://portal.brooklyn.edu via the Career Tab.  Join us on Facebook and Twitter, too! http://career.brooklyn.cuny.edu  ------------------------------------------------------------ To manage your subscription to Brooklyn College eAlerts, please visit https://websql.brooklyn.cuny.edu/eAlerts Brooklyn College is located at 2900 Bedford Ave, Brooklyn, NY 11210. Phone: 718-951-5000

message: Thank you for using our Marketplace Payments by Amazon service.  We are writing to let you know that payments have been made into your Marketplace Payments account. However, we are unable to transfer funds from your Marketplace Payments account because we do not have banking information for your account.  All funds resulting from the sales of merchandise or services that were paid for through the use of Marketplace Payments can only be transferred to your checking account.  Please log into your seller account and enter your checking account information now so that we may transfer the funds to you:  1.  Go to your Seller Account at www.amazon.com/seller-account. 2.  Click the "Seller Account Information" link under the Settings heading. 3.  In the "Deposit Method" section, click the Add button. 4.  Enter your checking account details and click the Submit button.  Your future Marketplace Payments disbursements will be submitted to this new checking account. Once a disbursement has been initiated, it may take up to 5 business days for the transfer to your checking account to be completed.  All sellers must wait 14 days for their first disbursement to be initiated. In addition, checking account information must be on file for a full 24 hours before an automatic disbursement is initiated.  Once the initial 14-day hold has passed, you may manually request disbursements as often as once every 24 hours, as long as 7 days have passed since checking information was entered.  Remember, providing a checking account is the only way you can receive your earnings. We cannot send checks, credit your credit card, or credit your retail account at this time.  To view details about our Marketplace Payments service, please visit the following URL:  http://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=1161250  Thank you for selling on Amazon.com.  Best regards,  Marketplace Payments by Amazon http://www.amazon.com

subject: FW: College students: Become a CAMERA campus fellow!
message: Friends, There is a war going on in college campuses for hearts and minds. Are you a college student who cares about the campus propaganda against Israel?  Do you have a son, daughter, grandchild, or other relative or friend who is? Please read and forward this information. Applications being considered now for The Legacy Heritage CAMERA Campus Fellows Program!=20 Deadline: July 1, 2010 Best, Naomi ________________________________________ Apply Now For The Legacy Heritage CAMERA Campus Fellows Program  COMMITTEE FOR ACCURACY IN MIDDLE EAST REPORTING IN AMERICA  Please spread the word to family and friends who might be interested in this vital program. =20  CAMERA seeks committed undergraduate students with excellent communication and leadership skills to become Legacy Heritage CAMERA Fellows for the 2010-2011 school year. At a time of intense campus activism related to the Middle East, CAMERA Fellows are a vital force in helping educate others and counter misinformation and bias.=20 CAMERA Fellows earn $1000 and a free, one-of-a-kind trip to Israel.=20 The position requires Fellows to:=20 =15 Organize 3-4 educational, pro-Israel programs during the school year  =15 Monitor and respond to Israel-related articles in the campus and local press=20 =15 Write Op-Eds and letters to educate others on the facts about Israel =15 Create a network of media activists=20 =15 Distribute CAMERA magazines and literature=20 =15 Participate in conference calls with other CAMERA Fellows and CAMERA staff  =15 Travel to Israel for intensive leadership training=20 Gain valuable experience, build your leadership skills and defend Israel on your campus! Contact Aviva Slomich at aviva@camera.org with any questions. Click here for application. =20  With thanks, Aviva Slomich National Student Coordinator www.camera.org www.camera.org =20 To subscribe to CAMERA's E-Mail Team alerts, send a note with your name, address, email, telephone number and how you heard about these alerts to alert@camera.org.  To unsubscribe, reply to this message with "unsubscribe" in the subject line.=20  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------  For more articles,please visit my Web page at: http://www.NaomiRagen.com To subscribe,   send a blank message to NaomiRagen-on@mail-list.com To unsubscribe, send a blank message to NaomiRagen-off@mail-list.com To change your email address, send a message to NaomiRagen-change@mail-list.com     with your old address in the Subject: line To contact the list owner, send your message to=20    NaomiRagen-list-owner@mail-list.com  mail-list.com    1302 Waugh Dr. #438    Houston, Texas    77019    USA  To unsubscribe, or change your email address, click here. http://cgi.mail-list.com/u?ln=3Dnaomiragen&nm=3Dchave%40designsbyfmc.com  This message was launched into cyberspace to chave@designsbyfmc.com

subject: Your Amazon.com Seller Account
message: Hello from Amazon.com,  Per your request, the bank account information associated with your seller account has been changed. All of your future disbursements will be submitted to this new bank account. This change will not affect any disbursement initiated prior to this change.  Note that if you are a new seller and are entering your bank account information for the first time, there is an initial 14-day holding period before funds will be released from your Marketplace Payments account.   In the future, whenever you update your bank account information, there is a 7-day holding period before funds will be released from your Marketplace Payments account.   These holding periods are important security requirements and we appreciate your patience.  You can update your bank account information at any time in the Settings section of your Seller Account.   For additional information, please visit our online Help pages.  Regards,  Amazon.com Payments
